        "title": "FAQ — Mineral Science",
        "items": [
            {
                "question": "Which mineral form is best?",
                "answer": "It depends on the mineral and purpose. Ionic is often most bioavailable, but stability and dosing matter too."
            },
            {
                "question": "How do I know if a mineral product is ionic?",
                "answer": "Check if it conducts electricity (EC/TDS meter) and is clear (not turbid). True ionic solutions are transparent."
            },
            {
                "question": "Why focus on sulfate?",
                "answer": "Sulfate is one of the most important and well-studied anions. It's a great starting point for mineral understanding."
